# Deployment & Release Conventions

## Version numbers are managed by CI/CD — never bump them manually

The `Manually Deploy New Version` GitHub Actions workflow runs `deploy/increment.sh` which automatically increments the version in:
- `wpmktgengine-woocommerce.php` (plugin header `Version:`)
- `readme.txt` (`Stable tag:`)

**Do not touch version numbers or `Stable tag` in PRs.** Only update the changelog in `readme.txt`.

```php
// ❌ NEVER do this in a PR
Version: 1.7.55

// ✅ ONLY update the changelog section
== 1.7.55 ==
Description of changes.
```

## Changelog entries are still required in PRs

Add a new entry at the top of the `== Changelog ==` section in `readme.txt` using the *next expected* version number as a placeholder. The CI/CD process will ensure the final version matches.

## PR workflow

1. Branch from `master`
2. Make changes
3. Add changelog entry to `readme.txt` (no version bump elsewhere)
4. Commit and push branch
5. Raise PR — conflicts on `Stable tag` are caused by the GenooBot release commit and should always resolve to our new version number, fixing any `11.x.xx` typos GenooBot introduces
